SIMPLE: upholder
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upholder
<hw>Up*hold"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Up</ets> +
<ets>holder.</ets> Cf. <er>Upholsterer</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A broker or auctioneer; a tradesman.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An undertaker, or provider for funerals.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>upholder</qex>, rueful harbinger of death.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An upholsterer.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One who, or that which, upholds; a supporter; a
defender; a sustainer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upholster</ent>⟦br⟧
